#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:6
msgid "Installing and Using plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section talks about installing and using third party plugins. For "
"writing your own plugins, please refer to :ref:`writing-plugins`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:11
msgid "Installing a third party plugin can be easily done with ``pip``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:13
msgid ""
"pip install pytest-NAME\n"
"pip uninstall pytest-NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:16
msgid ""
"If a plugin is installed, ``pytest`` automatically finds and integrates it, "
"there is no need to activate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:19
msgid "Here is a little annotated list for some popular plugins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:23
msgid ""
"`pytest-django <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-django>`_: write tests "
"for `django`_ apps, using pytest integration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:26
msgid ""
"`pytest-twisted <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-twisted>`_: write tests "
"for `twisted <http://twistedmatrix.com>`_ apps, starting a reactor and "
"processing deferreds from test functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:30
msgid ""
"`pytest-catchlog <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-catchlog>`_: to capture "
"and assert about messages from the logging module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:33
msgid ""
"`pytest-cov <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-cov>`_: coverage reporting, "
"compatible with distributed testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:36
msgid ""
"`pytest-xdist <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-xdist>`_: to distribute "
"tests to CPUs and remote hosts, to run in boxed mode which allows to survive "
"segmentation faults, to run in looponfailing mode, automatically re-running "
"failing tests on file changes, see also :ref:`xdist`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:42
msgid ""
"`pytest-instafail <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-instafail>`_: to "
"report failures while the test run is happening."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:45
msgid ""
"`pytest-bdd <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-bdd>`_ and `pytest-konira "
"<http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-konira>`_ to write tests using behaviour-"
"driven testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:49
msgid ""
"`pytest-timeout <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-timeout>`_: to timeout "
"tests based on function marks or global definitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:52
msgid ""
"`pytest-pep8 <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-pep8>`_: a ``--pep8`` "
"option to enable PEP8 compliance checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:55
msgid ""
"`pytest-flakes <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-flakes>`_: check source "
"code with pyflakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:58
msgid ""
"`oejskit <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/oejskit>`_: a plugin to run javascript "
"unittests in live browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:61
msgid ""
"To see a complete list of all plugins with their latest testing status "
"against different py.test and Python versions, please visit `plugincompat "
"<http://plugincompat.herokuapp.com/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:65
msgid ""
"You may also discover more plugins through a `pytest- pypi.python.org "
"search`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:72
msgid "Requiring/Loading plugins in a test module or conftest file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:74
msgid "You can require plugins in a test module or a conftest file like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:76
msgid "pytest_plugins = \"myapp.testsupport.myplugin\","
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:78
msgid ""
"When the test module or conftest plugin is loaded the specified plugins will "
"be loaded as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:81
msgid "pytest_plugins = \"myapp.testsupport.myplugin\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:83
msgid "which will import the specified module as a ``pytest`` plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:88
msgid "Finding out which plugins are active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:90
msgid ""
"If you want to find out which plugins are active in your environment you can "
"type::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:93
msgid "py.test --trace-config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:95
msgid ""
"and will get an extended test header which shows activated plugins and their "
"names. It will also print local plugins aka :ref:`conftest.py <conftest>` "
"files when they are loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:102
msgid "Deactivating / unregistering a plugin by name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:104
msgid "You can prevent plugins from loading or unregister them::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:106
msgid "py.test -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:108
msgid ""
"This means that any subsequent try to activate/load the named plugin will "
"not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:111
msgid ""
"If you want to unconditionally disable a plugin for a project, you can add "
"this option to your ``pytest.ini`` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:114
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:119
msgid ""
"Alternatively to disable it only in certain environments (for example in a "
"CI server), you can set ``PYTEST_ADDOPTS`` environment variable to ``-p no:"
"name``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:123
msgid "See :ref:`findpluginname` for how to obtain the name of a plugin."
msgstr ""

